  "notes": "Southern Altai (Turkic, Altai Republic), written in a Cyrillic alphabet = the Russian alphabet plus ⟨ј⟩ /dʒ~ɟ/, ⟨ҥ⟩ /ŋ/, ⟨ӧ⟩ /ø/, ⟨ӱ⟩ /y/. Vowel harmony (front/back, rounding) operates throughout; vowel length is phonemic and written by doubling. ⟨ф х ц щ ъ ь⟩ occur essentially only in Russian loanwords; the silent signs ⟨ъ⟩ and ⟨ь⟩ are omitted from the grapheme map. ⟨е ё ю я⟩ are the Russian iotated letters.",
